<TITLE> Barisal launch strike enters second day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)  Launch and ferry movements along 18 routes of the southern Barisal division were suspended for a second day on Monday after water transport workers called an indefinite strike the day before. Water transport on the Dhaka-Barisal route, however, was operating as normal, said Abu Saleh Quaiyum, an official of Barisal river port. Quaiyum also said that Barisal mayor Shawkat Hossain Hiron had held a meeting with the striking workers. Barisal Launch Labourers Association called the strike on Sunday protesting the removal of three fellow workers. The strikers told bdnews24.com earlier that three workers of the launch MV Chandradwip were suspended on Feb 24 following a confrontation with the vessel's owner Md Panna. Two were allowed to return to work after they apologised to the owner, but the third suspension order was not withdrawn, said fellow workers. The labourers association president, Shah Alam, told bdnews24.com said that they had held several meetings with the owner's representatives but there was no positive outcome. He said they were continuing their strike until they reached a satisfactory solution. MV Chandradwip owner Panna said he would accept the decision of the Barisal Launch Owners Association, but could not say whether the owners association would hold further talks with the labourers association. Launch workers said they would withdraw the strike if their leaders came to a decision. bdn
